      <hedline>
        <hl1>BRAZIL UNEMPLOYMENT FALLS</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Jennifer L. Rich</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Rich, Jennifer L</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Brazil's unemployment rate fell to 7.1 percent in August from 7.2 percent in July and 7.7 percent in August 1999; graph (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>In another sign that Brazil's economic expansion is gaining momentum, the unemployment rate decreased in August for a fifth consecutive month. Data from the National Statistics showed the rate fell to 7.1 percent from 7.2 percent in July and 7.7 percent in August 1999, reflecting stepped-up investment by industries in anticipation of stronger demand.</p>
        <p>Jennifer L. Rich</p>
      </block>
